building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: The centre of Shallyan worship. Its magical waters are said to have been poured from the goddess's chalice, that which granted Ranald immortality, and which is perhaps even the Grail itself. Countless pilgrims travel here in the hopes of being cured of the deadliest afflictions.
While the Archecclesiatium is technically the governing council of Myrmidia's cult, it has become the main temple's name by association.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Aunque el Archecclesiatium es técnicamente el consejo de gobierno del culto de Myrmidia, se ha convertido en el nombre del templo principal por asociación.

campaign_effect_scopes_localised_text_fo.value_original: \\n(own and allied armies in circle of influence)
campaign_effect_scopes_localised_text_fo.value_translated: \\n(ejércitos propios y aliados en el círculo de influencia)

campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_original: Let the captains decide. You can expect captives to be executed, humiliated and sent running, or sold as slaves. The foe may not appreciate it, but the troops will.
campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_translated: Deja que los capitanes decidan. Puedes esperar que los cautivos sean ejecutados, humillados y enviados corriendo, o vendidos como esclavos. Puede que el enemigo no lo aprecie, pero las tropas sí.

campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_original: We are not here for unnecessary bloodshed. It’s the civil thing to do, and hired mercenaries don’t like bad blood.
campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_translated: No estamos aquí para derramamientos de sangre innecesarios. Es lo civilizado, y a los mercenarios a sueldo no les gusta la mala sangre.

campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_original: Show the shackled creatures around and even send back them home for a parade! Everybody likes seeing humiliated evil.
campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_translated: Muestra a las criaturas encadenadas e incluso envíalas de vuelta a casa para un desfile. A todo el mundo le gusta ver al mal humillado.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: No cheese, but you gotta have garlic
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: No queso, pero tienes que tener ajo
Mi madre siempre usaba manteca de cerdo

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Give them to whoever can read this mess
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Dáselos a quien pueda leer este lío

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: We should send someone capable of discerning if the individual is dangerous or not.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Debemos enviar a alguien capaz de discernir si el individuo es peligroso o no.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: They can't all be that dangerous, can they? We can use a wizard.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: No todos pueden ser tan peligrosos, ¿verdad? Podemos usar un mago.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Trying to make sense of it without being able to ask the author is a waste of time. Might as well make some money.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Tratar de encontrarle sentido sin poder preguntarle al autor es una pérdida de tiempo. Mejor ganar algo de dinero.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Maybe there is something that can be useful in that mess.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Quizá haya algo que pueda ser útil en ese lío.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: A lot of artists and thinkers seem interested in the notes, perhaps a communal effort can at least spark some ideas.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Muchos artistas y pensadores parecen interesados en las notas, quizá un esfuerzo común pueda al menos suscitar algunas ideas.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: The only way is forward. Let's expand the network into the neighbouring countries.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: El único camino es hacia adelante. Ampliemos la red a los países vecinos.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Let other Merchant Princes handle this. They will obviously profit from it, but we'll secure a few favours down the line.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Deja que otros Príncipes Mercaderes se ocupen de esto. Obviamente se beneficiarán de ello, pero nos aseguraremos algunos favores más adelante.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Let's make sure everything is as profitable and solid as it can get before we move on.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Asegurémonos de que todo es lo más rentable y sólido posible antes de seguir adelante.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: With so much money flowing at grabbing distance, the temptation is strong and the benefits would be immediate...
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Con tanto dinero fluyendo a distancia, la tentación es fuerte y los beneficios serían inmediatos...

character_skills_localised_description_b.value_original: An orc that has been shot down is an orc that isn't going to chop anybody.
character_skills_localised_description_b.value_translated: Un orco abatido es un orco que no va a matar a nadie.

character_skills_localised_description_b.value_original: Behind each safe child in the towns there is a Ranger that has bled for him.
character_skills_localised_description_b.value_translated: Detrás de cada niño a salvo en las ciudades hay un Ranger que ha sangrado por él.

character_skills_localised_description_b.value_original: Losing the initiative is losing the battle.
character_skills_localised_description_b.value_translated: Perder la iniciativa es perder la batalla.

character_skills_localised_description_b.value_original: Limited numbers and overwhelming foes require unorthodox combat tactics.
character_skills_localised_description_b.value_translated: Los números limitados y los enemigos abrumadores requieren tácticas de combate poco ortodoxas.

character_skills_localised_description_b.value_original: Out here, only the toughest survive.
character_skills_localised_description_b.value_translated: Aquí sólo sobreviven los más duros.

character_skills_localised_description_b.value_original: "I shall wear midnight... and many knives."
character_skills_localised_description_b.value_translated: "Me vestiré de medianoche... y con muchos cuchillos".

character_skills_localised_description_b.value_original: The enemy might expect the old "What is that?!" trick, but there are other ways to distract them.
character_skills_localised_description_b.value_translated: El enemigo puede esperar el viejo truco de "¡¿Qué es eso?!", pero hay otras formas de distraerlo.

character_skills_localised_description_b.value_original: Getting to shoot or otherwise ambush an unaware enemy is an art of its own. Just like cutting throats.
character_skills_localised_description_b.value_translated: Conseguir disparar o emboscar a un enemigo desprevenido es un arte en sí mismo. Igual que cortar gargantas.

character_skills_localised_description_b.value_original: A horse can outrun Orcs, Trolls, even Giants. Not arrows. Or Doom Divers. But it still helps.
character_skills_localised_description_b.value_translated: Un caballo puede dejar atrás Orcos, Trolls, incluso Gigantes. No flechas. O Doom Divers. Pero aún así ayuda.

character_skills_localised_description_b.value_original: Persuading a Warboss to flee is much easier with a repeater rifle from the Empire. Expensive, but worth it.
character_skills_localised_description_b.value_translated: Persuadir a un Jefe de Guerra para que huya es mucho más fácil con un rifle de repetición del Imperio. Caro, pero vale la pena.

character_skills_localised_description_e.value_original: Chaos Worshippers and mutants are anathema to everything sacred. Cutting them to ribbons is the first step towards purity.
character_skills_localised_description_e.value_translated: Los adoradores del Caos y los mutantes son un anatema para todo lo sagrado. Cortarlos en tiras es el primer paso hacia la pureza.

character_skills_localised_description_e.value_original: "Kill them all. For the gods know those that are their own."
character_skills_localised_description_e.value_translated: "Matadlos a todos. Porque los dioses saben quiénes son los suyos".

character_skills_localised_description_e.value_original: Someone might dub it psychotic complex, but who knows what those shadows are plotting? This Lord does.
character_skills_localised_description_e.value_translated: Alguien podría calificarlo de complejo psicótico, pero ¿quién sabe lo que traman esas sombras? Este Señor sí.

character_skills_localised_description_e.value_original: With unfailing accuracy, the Inquisitor declares his target a sinner and heretic beyond repentance.
character_skills_localised_description_e.value_translated: Con una precisión infalible, el Inquisidor declara a su objetivo pecador y hereje más allá del arrepentimiento.

character_skills_localised_description_e.value_original: There are special kinds of heresy that should be treated from atop a large and overprotective mount. With big talons.
character_skills_localised_description_e.value_translated: Hay tipos especiales de herejía que deben tratarse desde lo alto de una montura grande y sobreprotectora. Con grandes garras.

character_skills_localised_description_e.value_original: At times, heresy is so well-radicated that it must be extinguished not from a tribunal but with an army.
character_skills_localised_description_e.value_translated: A veces, la herejía está tan arraigada que debe ser extinguida no desde un tribunal, sino con un ejército.

character_skills_localised_description_e.value_original: This Inquisitor shows an healthy mistrust towards magic users, and his entourage from the Cult makes sure there is no such petty interference from the enemy.
character_skills_localised_description_e.value_translated: Este Inquisidor muestra una sana desconfianza hacia los usuarios de magia, y su séquito del Culto se asegura de que no haya interferencias tan insignificantes por parte del enemigo.

character_skills_localised_description_e.value_original: It is known that people do not expect the Estalian Inquisition. When its emissaries are mounted on warhorses, they should be expected sooner at any rate.
character_skills_localised_description_e.value_translated: Es sabido que la gente no espera a la Inquisición estaliana. Cuando sus emisarios van montados en caballos de guerra, en todo caso hay que esperarlos antes.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Even the lousiest commander knows that you need two halves of a pair of scissors.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Hasta el comandante más pésimo sabe que se necesitan dos mitades de unas tijeras.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "You kill them before they kill you, sonnie. That's all it is."
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "Mátalos antes de que te maten, hijo. Eso es todo".

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "Though of course, if they do stab you, you better know how to parry."
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "Aunque, por supuesto, si te apuñalan, más vale que sepas parar".

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "Look, at the end of the day, you may be alive and you better learn from what didn't kill you."
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "Mira, al final del día, puede que estés vivo y será mejor que aprendas de lo que no te mató".

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "And to do that, it helps if you put all your weight where it counts."
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "Y para ello, ayuda que pongas todo tu peso donde cuenta".

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "Plus, you better kill them dead with the one shot you have."
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "Además, más vale que los mates de un tiro".

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Well, this is straightforward enough.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Esto es bastante sencillo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Oh wait, there's another chapter.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Oh, espera, hay otro capítulo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Duck! Shoot! Duck! Shoot! Shoot- shoot, that was wrong.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: ¡Agáchate! ¡Dispara! ¡Agáchate! ¡Disparen! Dispara... dispara, eso estuvo mal.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: The key is not letting your initiative depend on a lucky die.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: La clave es no dejar que tu iniciativa dependa de un dado afortunado.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: It's seldom enough to have only some of your troops to be ready to take a beating. The enemy has their own plans.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Rara vez basta con que algunas de tus tropas estén preparadas para recibir una paliza. El enemigo tiene sus propios planes.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Borgio has always cared for the needs of his troops, even the lowest mercs, and minded where they deployed them. Trust goes both ways.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Borgio siempre se ha preocupado por las necesidades de sus tropas, incluso de los mercenarios más bajos, y le ha importado dónde las desplegaban. La confianza va en ambos sentidos.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Borgio has no time for being wounded by his enemies. Not even by forks.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Borgio no tiene tiempo para ser herido por sus enemigos. Ni siquiera por los tenedores.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Most things simply do not stand for long when Borgio is set to conquer them.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: La mayoría de las cosas no resisten mucho tiempo cuando Borgio se dispone a conquistarlas.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Borgio knows the worth of a well-trained and well-protected force of versatile crossbowmen. Let Miragliano be known for a fearsome force of troops that can block well, fight well and shoot back!
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Borgio conoce el valor de una fuerza bien entrenada y protegida de ballesteros versátiles. Que Miragliano sea conocido por una temible fuerza de tropas que saben bloquear bien, luchar bien y responder a los disparos.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Battles are a matter of applying force to the weakest point. The tougher the force, the louder the crack.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Las batallas consisten en aplicar la fuerza al punto más débil. Cuanto más dura sea la fuerza, más fuerte será el crujido.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Only some scholars might know what those statues were about, but once melted and used to forge this huge brazen armour, they might have brought over whatever enchantment they used to bear...
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Sólo algunos eruditos sabrán de qué eran esas estatuas, pero una vez fundidas y utilizadas para forjar esta enorme armadura de bronce, podrían haber traído consigo cualquier encantamiento que llevaran...

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Steel barding adds that certain something to your mount. A pity they didn't have it in red.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: La armadura de acero le da un toque especial a tu montura. Lástima que no lo tuvieran en rojo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: During the Siege of Remas, a cannonball flew straight at Borgio. Instead of rather influential smithereens, bystanders witnessed that the projectile was stuck right into the Prince's armour, who was barely wounded. Melted and reshaped as a mace, the cannonball makes for a terrifying and symbolic weapon.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Durante el asedio de Remas, una bala de cañón voló directamente hacia Borgio. En lugar de hacerse añicos, los espectadores fueron testigos de que el proyectil se clavó justo en la armadura del príncipe, que apenas resultó herido. Fundida y remodelada como maza, la bala de cañón constituye un arma aterradora y simbólica.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: During the most furious melees, Borgio wears his frightening mask, a grotesque grimace of malice. Coupled with the wearer's bulk and might, the effect is scary indeed.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Durante los combates más furiosos, Borgio lleva su aterradora máscara, una grotesca mueca de malicia. Junto con el volumen y la fuerza de su portador, el efecto es realmente aterrador.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: A horse! A horse! An acceptable amount of florins for a horse!
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: ¡Un caballo! ¡Un caballo! ¡Una cantidad aceptable de florines por un caballo!

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Whatever the enemy, Cadavo is unsubtle in his subtlety and will exploit any possible trick to vex the enemy. His troops are veteran harriers and have learned from the best.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Sea cual sea el enemigo, Cadavo es poco sutil y explotará cualquier artimaña posible para vejar al enemigo. Sus tropas son aguiluchos veteranos y han aprendido de los mejores.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: It doesn't matter if they have gambling issues or if their perception of property is somewhat challenged. These men are the best fighters around Cadavo.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: No importa si tienen problemas con el juego o si su percepción de la propiedad está algo cuestionada. Estos hombres son los mejores luchadores de Cadavo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Cadavo's usual bunch also tends to dispatch opponents as quickly as possible, since in a dangerous New World the least dangerous foe is a trained Elf. Or maybe they just like hurting stuff.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: El grupo habitual de Cadavo también tiende a despachar a sus oponentes lo antes posible, ya que en un Nuevo Mundo peligroso el enemigo menos peligroso es un elfo entrenado. O puede que simplemente les guste hacer daño.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: El Cadavo is a feared and inspiring figure in three continents. However, some would rather snuff his existence altogether.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: El Cadavo es una figura temida e inspiradora en dos continentes. Sin embargo, algunos preferirían acabar con su existencia.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: It is with one of nature's tricks that Cadavo created one Duke Arrenault's hardship. It was El Cadavo, still in Tilea, that originally happened to destroy Rodrigo Delmonte's lands, which in turn prompted the latter to start what ended up as the Alcatani Fellowship. In one of the company's campaigns, it was Duke Arrenault's turn to fall in the dust, losing his knights, his feud and his eye to the Tilean pikes. A fallen knight by fate and attitude, Arrenault goes renegade in search for the tools for vengeance.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Es con uno de los trucos de la naturaleza que Cadavo creó una de las penurias del Duque Arrenault. Fue El Cadavo, aún en Tilea, quien originalmente pasó a destruir las tierras de Rodrigo Delmonte, lo que a su vez impulsó a este último a iniciar lo que acabó siendo la Hermandad Alcatani. En una de las campañas de la compañía, le tocó al duque Arrenault caer en el polvo, perdiendo sus caballeros, su feudo y su ojo a manos de las picas tileanas. Caballero caído por destino y actitud, Arrenault se vuelve renegado en busca de las herramientas para la venganza.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Arrenault is in Estalia, trying to gather what men and resources he can against the Alcatani and their masters. He is out of luck until he is mistaken for the famous El Cadavo, whose successful persona he promptly abuses to lead what turns out being an overseas expedition. Arrenault ends up in the New World, growing into the figure of a ruthless mercenary commander, accruing a large retinue of adventurers and even other disillusioned Bretonnians. Almost as he reckoned his resources to be enough for his vendetta, the real Cadavo, also in the New World, gets wind of the impostor. El Cadavo and Arrenault start a slithery game of hunted and hunter until their forces collide under a showering monsoon. The battle is fierce and chaotic, yet the two leaders finally manage to meet each other in a fierce and one-eyed duel in the undergrowth. In the exhausted silence of a dying battle, a fateful pistol shot rings among the rain sprays.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Arrenault está en Estalia, intentando reunir los hombres y recursos que puede contra los Alcatani y sus amos. No tiene suerte hasta que lo confunden con el famoso El Cadavo, de cuyo exitoso personaje abusa para liderar lo que resulta ser una expedición a ultramar. Arrenault acaba en el Nuevo Mundo, convirtiéndose en la figura de un despiadado comandante mercenario, acumulando un gran séquito de aventureros e incluso de otros bretones desilusionados. Casi cuando consideraba que sus recursos eran suficientes para su venganza, el verdadero Cadavo, también en el Nuevo Mundo, se entera de la existencia del impostor. El Cadavo y Arrenault inician un escurridizo juego de cazado y cazador hasta que sus fuerzas chocan bajo un lluvioso monzón. La batalla es feroz y caótica, pero los dos líderes consiguen finalmente enfrentarse en un duelo feroz y tuerto entre la maleza. En el silencio exhausto de una batalla agonizante, un fatídico disparo de pistola resuena entre las salpicaduras de la lluvia.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Renegades, adventurers and mercenaries stop fighting as one, as the monsoon also stops its apparently tireless attempt at turning the place into a swamp. A couple of minutes later, Cadavo emerges from the jungle, bloodied yet satisfied, for the challenger is dead, head caved in by the bullet. He raises Arrenault's crest, the trophy upon which he scratches his victory mark, as the survivors from both armies cheer the victor, for this is how things often go among such fighters. He adds the crest to the lot of other charms and trophies he carries, and reassembles his troops for whatever the future awaits.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Renegados, aventureros y mercenarios dejan de luchar al unísono, al tiempo que el monzón detiene también su aparentemente incansable intento de convertir el lugar en un pantano. Un par de minutos después, Cadavo emerge de la jungla, ensangrentado pero satisfecho, pues el retador está muerto, con la cabeza hundida por la bala. Levanta el escudo de Arrenault, el trofeo en el que ha grabado su marca de victoria, mientras los supervivientes de ambos ejércitos aclaman al vencedor, pues así es como suelen ir las cosas entre estos luchadores. Añade el escudo al lote de otros amuletos y trofeos que lleva consigo, y vuelve a reunir a sus tropas para lo que les espere en el futuro.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Only a few of the defeated are killed: there aren't many other ways to get rid of troublemakers so far away from provisions and what passes as civilization. And yet the survivors' hearts are high, because even if the day was bloody and wet, the pay is going to be excellent, the future looks bright for they are the best troops ever assembled in the Colonies, under a legendary Condottiero that has just defeated an upstart rival and that now only intends to restock and start what promises to be a fruitful adventure in a ripe land.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Sólo unos pocos de los derrotados son asesinados: no hay muchas otras formas de deshacerse de los alborotadores tan lejos de las provisiones y de lo que pasa por civilización. Y sin embargo, los supervivientes tienen el corazón en alto, porque aunque la jornada haya sido sangrienta y húmeda, la paga va a ser excelente, el futuro se presenta brillante, pues son las mejores tropas jamás reunidas en las Colonias, a las órdenes de un Condottiero legendario que acaba de derrotar a un rival advenedizo y que ahora sólo pretende reabastecerse y comenzar lo que promete ser una fructífera aventura en una tierra madura.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: That he would lead the greatest adventuring army ever assembled, that he would trample any opposition in this New World and in the Old World. That he would never forget his past and learn from it, for the future challenges will likely demand each grain of his ability.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Que lideraría el mayor ejército aventurero jamás reunido, que pisotearía cualquier oposición en este Nuevo Mundo y en el Viejo Mundo. Que nunca olvidaría su pasado y aprendería de él, pues los desafíos futuros probablemente exigirán cada grano de su habilidad.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: That he is El Cadavo, the greatest mercenary commander to ever exist, a rock against the ebbs and tides of the ruthless world, and that he will be just as merciless for the world is his for the taking, and for anybody who would follow him to glory.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Que él es El Cadavo, el más grande comandante mercenario que jamás haya existido, una roca contra los vaivenes del despiadado mundo, y que será igual de despiadado, porque el mundo es suyo, y para cualquiera que le siga hacia la gloria.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: A Duke was just another notch on Cadavo's blades, just another scar on his face. The figure of Cadavo was born in the heat of politics and battle, had matured in incredible stories and then into myth. The clever would notice that Cadavo's stories are centuries old, scattered in space and time and yet mostly true. Someone whispers that he is immortal, that his is only a title, that he cannot just be a mercenary commander. Be that as it may, Arrenault's apparent demise will just fuel Cadavo's legend and add another paragraph to fireside stories.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Un Duque era sólo otra muesca en las espadas de Cadavo, sólo otra cicatriz en su rostro. La figura de Cadavo había nacido en el fragor de la política y la batalla, había madurado en historias increíbles y luego en mito. Los avispados se darían cuenta de que las historias de Cadavo tienen siglos de antigüedad, están dispersas en el espacio y el tiempo y, sin embargo, son en su mayoría ciertas. Alguien susurra que es inmortal, que lo suyo es sólo un título, que no puede ser sólo un comandante mercenario. Sea como fuere, la aparente desaparición de Arrenault no hará sino alimentar la leyenda de Cadavo y añadir otro párrafo a las historias de hogueras.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: An amulet made of a weird alloy, capable of neutralizing poisons and many of the magical properties for weapons that would injure the bearer.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Un amuleto hecho de una extraña aleación, capaz de neutralizar venenos y muchas de las propiedades mágicas de las armas que podrían herir al portador.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: You may not like it, but this is what peak performance looks like.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Puede que no te guste, pero así es el rendimiento máximo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Cadavo will have his city. The fat toad will probably get tired of destroying it way before Cadavo is of trying.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Cadavo tendrá su ciudad. El sapo gordo probablemente se cansará de destruirla mucho antes de que Cadavo se canse de intentarlo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Cadavo has survived multiple military campaigns, an undefined number of duels, at least five magical armageddons and six mothers-in-law.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Cadavo ha sobrevivido a múltiples campañas militares, a un número indefinido de duelos, al menos a cinco armagedones mágicos y a seis suegras.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Cadavo's current steed is an ill-tempered gelding only loyal and tending to Cadavo. To those few he doesn't kick on sight, he answers to the name of Broccolo.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: El actual corcel de Cadavo es un castrado malhumorado que sólo es leal y cariñoso con Cadavo. Para los pocos a los que no patea nada más verlo, responde al nombre de Brócolo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Catrazza's political skills and calm demeanour has led a few to forget he once was an able captain of venture, and a quick fencer at that.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Las habilidades políticas y el comportamiento tranquilo de Catrazza han hecho que algunos olviden que una vez fue un hábil capitán de aventureros, y además un rápido esgrimista.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Money equals power, power equals money. Marinated in good manners and leverage, money can move mountains aside. And armies, especially armies.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Dinero es igual a poder, poder es igual a dinero. Marinado con buenos modales y apalancamiento, el dinero puede mover montañas a un lado. Y ejércitos, sobre todo ejércitos.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: The so-called Birdmen of Catrazza (no relations) are a weird lot, to be sure, but they are good at scouting and at getting out of tight spots.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Los llamados Hombres Pájaro de Catrazza (sin parentesco) son un grupo extraño, pero son buenos explorando y saliendo de apuros.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Catrazza's companies have gathered much fame as reliable and efficient skirmishers, able to bring victory against all odds.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Las compañías de Catrazza han adquirido mucha fama como escaramuzadores fiables y eficientes, capaces de llevar la victoria contra viento y marea.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: It is good to be friends with most of the armed nobles of the region, and to always know who was in whose bedroom.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Es bueno ser amigo de la mayoría de los nobles armados de la región, y saber siempre quién estaba en la alcoba de quién.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Respect my autoritah.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Respeta mi autoridad.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Once again, Tilea will be covered in marble and, most importantly, wealthy in money and people.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Una vez más, Tilea estará cubierta de mármol y, lo que es más importante, rica en dinero y personas.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Catrazza is not usually one for religious displays, but there are solid practical and diplomatical advantages for wearing this ring around.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: A Catrazza no le suelen gustar las exhibiciones religiosas, pero llevar este anillo tiene sólidas ventajas prácticas y diplomáticas.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: An ancient elven blade, relic of a time when Tilea was an Asur colony. Its wielder's attacks leave a glowing and elegant trail of light and molten armour.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Una antigua espada élfica, reliquia de una época en la que Tilea era una colonia Asur. Los ataques de su portador dejan un rastro brillante y elegante de luz y armadura fundida.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Good equipment may make the difference between competent and successful mercenaries, or competent and dead ones. Everything is an investment towards the future.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Un buen equipamiento puede marcar la diferencia entre mercenarios competentes y exitosos, o competentes y muertos. Todo es una inversión de futuro.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: A horse! A horse! An acceptable amount of florins for a horse!
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: ¡Un caballo! ¡Un caballo! ¡Una cantidad aceptable de florines por un caballo!

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Skink Priests like their prophetic mumbo-jumbo, but their needs are just as businesslike as anybody else's. And they pay in pearls as big as their eyes.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: A los Sacerdotes Skink les gusta su palabrería profética, pero sus necesidades son tan comerciales como las de cualquier otro. Y pagan con perlas tan grandes como sus ojos.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Managing to get an audience with an actual Slann is a big honour, to actually get them to notice you in those big fat plans of theirs is... a triumph.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Conseguir una audiencia con un Slann de verdad es un gran honor, pero conseguir que se fijen en ti en sus enormes planes es... un triunfo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Surprisingly, the local Slanns and Chiefs seem legitimately friendly now towards Colombo's expedition. There is a lot to learn just by being shown around their cities.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Sorprendentemente, los Slanns y Jefes locales parecen ahora legítimamente amistosos con la expedición de Colombo. Hay mucho que aprender sólo con que te enseñen sus ciudades.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Making friends with Skink interpreters isn't easy, but the more contacts you have, the more you understand each other, the more business can be done.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Hacer amistad con los intérpretes Skink no es fácil, pero cuantos más contactos tengas, cuanto más os entendáis, más negocios se podrán hacer.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: A reward from the Slann, this amulet in the shape of Sotek's tongue feels oddly alive and protected the wearer more times than he recalls.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Recompensa de los Slann, este amuleto con forma de lengua de Sotek se siente extrañamente vivo y ha protegido a su portador más veces de las que recuerda.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Marco Colombo is famous for having 'discovered' the New World, and for being one of the very few to have peaceful dealings with the Lizardmen.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Marco Colombo es famoso por haber "descubierto" el Nuevo Mundo y por ser uno de los pocos que han mantenido relaciones pacíficas con los Hombres Lagarto.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Used by someone to write an otherwise uninteresting map, this scroll bears potent enchantments of Nehekharan protective magic. However, it tends to crumble a bit with each use.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Utilizado por alguien para escribir un mapa poco interesante, este pergamino contiene potentes encantamientos de magia protectora nehekhariana. Sin embargo, tiende a desmoronarse un poco con cada uso.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Colombo's fame, and his army's, is growing. Even the most fearsome bandits and raiders tend to shuffle their feet upon learning they have become a target for Colombo's mercenaries.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: La fama de Colombo, y de su ejército, va en aumento. Incluso los bandidos y asaltantes más temibles tienden a arrastrar los pies al enterarse de que se han convertido en objetivo de los mercenarios de Colombo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Fine troops, personally drilled by Colombo, tend to become a devastating force on the battlefield.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Las buenas tropas, entrenadas personalmente por Colombo, tienden a convertirse en una fuerza devastadora en el campo de batalla.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "This baby can do zero to fifty in nothing! And I swear she can understand everything I- did she just write "sixty" with her hoof?"
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "¡Este bebé puede hacer de cero a cincuenta en nada! Y te juro que entiende todo lo que yo... ¿Acaba de escribir "sesenta" con la pezuña?".

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Until he is usurped, for these things tend to happen in Tilea and especially in Trantio, Colombo is still prince, with friends over there. Armoured friends.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Hasta que sea usurpado, pues estas cosas suelen pasar en Tilea y sobre todo en Trantio, Colombo sigue siendo príncipe, con amigos por allí. Amigos blindados.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: A lucky prey from a skirmish against Corsairs, this rare magical repeater crossbow is too cumbersome for use on foot, but if you want something positively dead, it's a nice toy. Just have to hope the magic in it isn't too dark.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Una presa afortunada de una escaramuza contra Corsarios, esta rara ballesta mágica de repetición es demasiado engorrosa para usarla a pie, pero si quieres algo positivamente muerto, es un bonito juguete. Solo tienes que esperar que la magia que contiene no sea demasiado oscura.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "Yes, I can see that is a Minotaur skull, my day hasn't improved one bit."
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "Sí, ya veo que es un cráneo de minotauro, mi día no ha mejorado ni un poquito".

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "Franco, I know you have only the one arm left, but if they say there are Chaos fellas around here it's everybody's problem, alright?"
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "Franco, sé que sólo te queda un brazo, pero si dicen que hay tipos del Caos por aquí es problema de todos, ¿de acuerdo?"

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "It's Corsairs again, boys. Say your prayers and remember they run faster than you do."
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "Son Corsarios de nuevo, muchachos. Recen sus oraciones y recuerden que corren más rápido que ustedes".

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "That's a pretty good impression of an orc, alright. We can do that, pal, just show us where they are."
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "Esa es una muy buena imitación de un orco, de acuerdo. Podemos hacerlo, amigo, sólo muéstranos dónde están".

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "That's a rat, right? Yes, that's a rat. I was worried you'd say that."
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "Eso es una rata, ¿verdad? Sí, es una rata. Me preocupaba que dijeras eso".

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "A skull. Walks like a drunk. Bites. Huinipachutli, mate, unless you're mimicking Giovanni I know what you mean."
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "Una calavera. Camina como un borracho. Muerde. Huinipachutli, colega, a menos que estés imitando a Giovanni, sé a lo que te refieres".

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: About as potent as orange juice to the Lizardmen, this precious lustrian wine is strong indeed for a human!
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Tan potente como el zumo de naranja para los hombres lagarto, este preciado vino lustriano es realmente fuerte para un humano.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: By a combination of inclination, faith and training, this character is aligned with the cults of Sister Fury, if not a member outright. One of Myrmidia's companions in life, Fury's legacy is one of intense, violent, but controlled rage and violence against injustice and destruction.

By a combination of inclination, faith and training, this character is aligned with the cults of the god Morr, if not a member outright. The old god of the dead's legacy is one of fatalism and certainty, and finds its largest seat in Luccini.

By a combination of inclination, faith and training, this character is aligned with the cults of the goddess Myrmidia, if not a member outright. Myrmidia is an ascended mortal and the chief deity in the south, and the vast influence of her cults teach tactical acumen, mercy, and civilization.

By a combination of inclination, faith and training, this character is aligned with the cults of Nahmud, if not a member outright. Although part of the vaster Myrmidian cults, the various sects of Nahmud favour equality and special education, and are somewhat too fond of secrecy.

By a combination of inclination, faith and training, this character is aligned with the cults of the god Ranald, if not a member outright. He is one of many and sometimes darker aspects, but the lord of fortune was also the only one who could make Morr smile. Somewhat.

By a combination of inclination, faith and training, this character is aligned with the cults of the goddess Shallya, if not a member outright. Her teachings of healing and compassion feel at odds with the world's grimness and darkness, which is also why many flock to her.

By a combination of inclination, faith and training, this character is aligned with the cults of the god Solkan, if not a member outright. The merciless god is one of the most ancient, and just as timeless is his unbridled retribution against the corrupted. His is currently a relatively awkward presence, strongest in Remas.

By a combination of inclination, faith and training, this character is aligned with the cults of the goddess Verena, if not a member outright. Like her husband Morr, the blind deity's legacy is not only one of learning and justice, but also one of detached impartiality.
It's good to have someone watching your back against foes looking for a cheap kill. Especially if they know everything about it.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Es bueno tener a alguien que te cubra las espaldas contra los enemigos que buscan una muerte barata. Sobre todo si lo saben todo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: A surgical strike at the enemy's sword-hand, and the duel ends before it has even begun.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Un golpe quirúrgico a la mano de la espada del enemigo, y el duelo termina antes de que haya empezado.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "What do you mean 'You killed my father, prepare to die'? How can you say that when there are about thirty-six pretenders to that role, by today's count! In guardia!"
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "¿Qué quieres decir con 'Has matado a mi padre, prepárate para morir'? ¡¿Cómo puedes decir eso cuando hay cerca de treinta y seis pretendientes a ese papel, según el recuento de hoy! ¡En guardia!"

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: The best Duellists tend to draw the attention of colleagues who'd love to challenge and learn from them, in a non-specific order.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Los mejores duelistas tienden a llamar la atención de colegas a los que les encantaría desafiarlos y aprender de ellos, en un orden no específico.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: [this is a dummy, dummy]
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: [this is a dummy, dummy]

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Not all of the really great duellists can dream of becoming a full-pledged Knight Encarmine, but certainly all the Knights Encarmine are great duellists.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: No todos los grandes duelistas pueden soñar con convertirse en un Caballeros Encarnados de pleno derecho, pero sin duda todos los Caballeros Encarnados son grandes duelistas.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: A parrying dagger won't protect you from darts, but a strike will never hurt you if you know your trigonometry.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Una daga de parada no te protegerá de los dardos, pero un golpe nunca te hará daño si conoces la trigonometría.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "You shoulda seen him, he was-a like a capitone! Kinda greasy, too."
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "Deberías haberlo visto, ¡era como un capitone! Y un poco grasiento".

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Duellists are usually more comfortable fighting on solid ground rather than on a snorting beast, but they are also adaptable people at heart.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Los duelistas suelen sentirse más cómodos luchando en tierra firme que sobre una bestia resoplando, pero también son personas adaptables en el fondo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: If Figuera is the father of fencing, Casanova is the impertinent grandchild. Like the adventurous teacher, the Duellist focuses on agility of foot and bedazzling assaults that put an end to the fight as soon as possible.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Si Figuera es el padre de la esgrima, Casanova es el nieto impertinente. Al igual que el maestro aventurero, el duelista se centra en la agilidad de pies y los asaltos deslumbrantes que ponen fin al combate lo antes posible.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: If Figuera is the father of fencing, Estevan is the bastard son. This Duellist uses the off-hand as a lightning-quick defensive tool.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Si Figuera es el padre de la esgrima, Estevan es el hijo bastardo. Este duelista utiliza la mano como herramienta defensiva.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: The Duellist is loyal to the teachings of the father of fencing, focused on balance.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: El duelista es fiel a las enseñanzas del padre de la esgrima, centradas en el equilibrio.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: A long mission outside the city requires to be locked and loaded. For Orcs.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Una larga misión fuera de la ciudad requiere ir cargado y preparado. Para Orcos.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Charge and fire with all weapons! They won't expect that.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Carga y dispara con todas las armas. No se lo esperarán.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Where there is a loaded pistol, there is hope.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Donde hay una pistola cargada, hay esperanza.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: The Duellist takes pause to analyse and criticise the opponent's fighting technique. The verbal assault is occasionally polite but always substantial.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: El duelista se detiene a analizar y criticar la técnica de combate del adversario. El ataque verbal es a veces cortés, pero siempre sustancial.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: With a last and complex flourish, the Duellist has a last word on the duel. The opponent likely wishes they were dead at this point.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Con una última y compleja floritura, el duelista dice su última palabra sobre el duelo. Es probable que el oponente desee estar muerto en este momento.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: It is poor form to duel someone without first introducing yourself. Of course, it's a good chance to make the opponent angry and clumsy.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Es de mala educación batirse en duelo con alguien sin antes presentarse. Por supuesto, es una buena oportunidad para enfadar y hacer torpe al oponente.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: The Duellist explains in detail, more or less politely and technically, how they'll win. More or less.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: El duelista explica detalladamente, de forma más o menos educada y técnica, cómo va a ganar. Más o menos.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: The old Sunscryer trusts the fellow human so very marginally more than he trusts the other races, and any common ground only propels his paranoia. Something about their foreigner habits and their filthy lingo.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: El anciano Sunscryer confía en los congéneres humanos muy muy poco más de lo que confía en las demás razas, y cualquier punto en común no hace sino impulsar su paranoia. Algo tiene que ver con sus costumbres extranjeras y su sucia jerga.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Unbeknownst to him, Sokth's curse pervading what is left of his body is only becoming stronger, more vengeful and contagious. Eventually, it will put an end to Eustaquio's unlife, but until then it's only corroborating his belief in a blessing of the gods.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Sin que él lo sepa, la maldición de Sokth que invade lo que queda de su cuerpo es cada vez más fuerte, vengativa y contagiosa. Con el tiempo, acabará con la vida de Eustaquio, pero hasta entonces sólo corrobora su creencia en una bendición de los dioses.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Eustaquio's presence at the lead of an army has an understandably perplexing effect on the troops, except on the most travelled of them. Some who have taken up odd customs abroad even tried to paint a pair of moustaches on the skull.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: La presencia de Eustaquio al frente de un ejército tiene un comprensible efecto desconcertante en las tropas, excepto en las más viajeras. Algunos que han tomado costumbres extrañas en el extranjero incluso intentaron pintarse un par de bigotes en el cráneo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "These End Times of yours, pffsh, the crops are not even failing that much. When I was young I had to fight off two thousand Arabyans just to get to my hors- WHERE ARE YOU GOING?"
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "Estos Tiempos Finales vuestros, pffsh, las cosechas ni siquiera están fallando tanto. Cuando era joven tuve que luchar contra dos mil arabeanos sólo para llegar a mis caballos... ¿A DÓNDE VAIS?"

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "Be like a spear, and have a point! Ah-ah!"
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "¡Sé como una lanza, y ten punta! ¡Ah-ah!"

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Ogres, Greenskins, Chaos Worshippers, all shall be punished for the destruction they perpetrate against Gashnagia.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Ogros, Pieles Verdes, Adoradores del Caos, todos serán castigados por la destrucción que perpetren contra Gashnagia.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: The fall of Ushoran's empire burns vivid in Gashnag's cultivated memories. The other bloodlines are not to be trusted, not even fellow Strigoi.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: La caída del imperio de Ushoran arde vívida en los recuerdos cultivados de Gashnag. No se puede confiar en los demás linajes, ni siquiera en los compañeros Strigoi.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Know thy enemy, and fight it with its own tools.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Conoce a tu enemigo y lucha contra él con sus propias herramientas.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Led from the front by their powerful and selfless Prince, the citizens of Gashnagia fight like one.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Liderados desde el frente por su poderoso y abnegado Príncipe, los ciudadanos de Gashnagia luchan como uno solo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Promoting conservative tactics, Gashnag preserves his subject's safety until melee is inevitable.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Promoviendo tácticas conservadoras, Gashnag preserva la seguridad de sus súbditos hasta que el combate cuerpo a cuerpo es inevitable.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Very personal aggressors find out too late that it is not easy to stab a powerful Strigoi cloaked in illusions.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Los agresores muy personales descubren demasiado tarde que no es fácil apuñalar a un poderoso Strigoi envuelto en ilusiones.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Everything stands on Gashnag not being recognized for what he is. As such, mages and agents have to be kept at a safe distance.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Todo depende de que Gashnag no sea reconocido por lo que es. Por ello, magos y agentes deben mantenerse a una distancia prudencial.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Even in his delusions, Gashnag knows that he doesn't need to conquer more lands to keep his own happy. Even if the neighbours don't know what they're talking to.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Incluso en sus delirios, Gashnag sabe que no necesita conquistar más tierras para mantener felices a los suyos. Aunque los vecinos no sepan con quién están hablando.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Seeding constant confusion among the opponents, the Black Prince protects his subjects from harm.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Al sembrar la confusión constante entre los oponentes, el Príncipe Negro protege a sus súbditos de cualquier daño.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Gashnag allows a few well-controlled ghouls and beasts to circle around his forces, attacking his foes and his foes only. Even if the wretched creatures are incredibly well-behaved for their type and ultimately fight on the humans' side, old habits die hard and many start connecting the dots.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Gashnag permite que unos cuantos engendros y bestias bien controlados rodeen a sus fuerzas, atacando a sus enemigos y sólo a sus enemigos. Aunque las desdichadas criaturas se comportan increíblemente bien para su tipo y en última instancia luchan del lado de los humanos, los viejos hábitos son difíciles de perder y muchos empiezan a conectar los puntos.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Knowledge is power, and this learning comes from the Strigoi patriarch's secrets and mistakes.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Aprender de los secretos y errores del patriarca de los Strigoi directamente de uno de sus artefactos supervivientes podría no tener precio.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: One of Ushoran's own artefacts, this polestaff supposedly allowed the original Strigoi patriarch to hold out the Lahmians' aggression for so long.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Uno de los artefactos del propio Ushoran, este bastón supuestamente permitió al patriarca Strigoi original resistir la agresión de los Lahmianos durante tanto tiempo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: It is said that a town ruled by Gashnag was being harassed by a group of Ogres. The Black Prince set out on his own, beneath his black cloak, and came back with the pillagers' heads, to be put on pikes.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Se dice que una ciudad gobernada por Gashnag estaba siendo acosada por un grupo de Ogros. El Príncipe Negro partió en solitario, bajo su capa negra, y regresó con las cabezas de los saqueadores, para colocarlas en picas.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Divine worship aside, Ushoran's empire was still fundamentally happy and loyal, which is fairly uncommon on its own right.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Dejando a un lado el culto divino, el imperio de Ushoran seguía siendo fundamentalmente feliz y leal, algo poco común por derecho propio.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: You take care of your mates, and they take care of you.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Tú cuidas de tus compañeros, y ellos cuidan de ti.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Men will always gather around the leader that is fighting for the well-being of their own country.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Los hombres siempre se reunirán en torno al líder que luche por el bienestar de su propio país.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: A Dwarf's grudge is forever, but so is his gratitude for many lives saved. The unexpected gift of a family runic axe is to be remembered for just as long.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: El rencor de un Enano es eterno, pero también lo es su gratitud por tantas vidas salvadas. El inesperado regalo de un hacha rúnica familiar será recordado durante el mismo tiempo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Being considered a true friend by the Dwarfs is a huge honour and benefit. As long as one keeps being careful not to offend them.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Ser considerado un verdadero amigo por los enanos es un gran honor y un beneficio. Siempre y cuando uno tenga cuidado de no ofenderlos.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: A rare arabyan Pegasus, gifted by Crusaders. A living and swift siphon of light and magic, ready to unleash their energy on aggressors.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Un raro pegaso árabe, regalado por los cruzados. Un sifón viviente y veloz de luz y magia, listo para desatar su energía sobre los agresores.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "You shoulda seen him! There was the troll behind him, right, raising its club, then Beardy turns around and buries his axe right in the thing's face! And down it goes! Who would have known dem damn stunties can move that quickly? Oh, hey Beardy!"
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "¡Deberías haberlo visto! Estaba el troll detrás de él, levantando su garrote, entonces Beardy se da la vuelta y le entierra su hacha justo en la cara. ¡Y cayó! ¿Quién iba a saber que los malditos aturdidores podían moverse tan rápido? ¡Hola, Beardy!

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Formerly a magic and fluttering arabyan turban, this souvenir bears energetic enchantments. The cadre of Myrmidian priests who prodded it for a week have testified that the scarf won't strangle Gausser of its own initiative anytime soon, which is oddly specific.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Antiguamente un mágico y revoloteante turbante arabyano, este souvenir porta enérgicos encantamientos. El grupo de sacerdotes mirmidianos que lo ha pinchado durante una semana ha atestiguado que el pañuelo no estrangulará a Gausser por iniciativa propia en un futuro próximo, lo que resulta extrañamente específico.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Sincere Dwarf warriors will defend your kin like their own. And teach your own fighters to fight like they do.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Sinceros guerreros enanos defenderán a los tuyos como si fueran suyos. Y enseñarán a tus propios combatientes a luchar como ellos.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Good warriors and equipment coming from the mountains, not only the poorest dwarf misfits and adventurers caught at a low ebb.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Buenos guerreros y equipo procedentes de las montañas, no sólo los más pobres enanos inadaptados y aventureros en horas bajas.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Gods know the Dwarfs are careful with their trade relationships. Especially with related payments. Favoured ties are to be cherished.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Los dioses saben que los Enanos son cuidadosos con sus relaciones comerciales. Especialmente con los pagos relacionados. Los lazos de favor deben ser apreciados.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: A horse! A horse! An acceptable amount of florins for a horse!
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: ¡Un caballo! ¡Un caballo! ¡Una cantidad aceptable de florines por un caballo!

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Personal friendships with the Dwarfs from the Holds are worth the general's weight in gold, armour or cannons.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: La amistad personal con los Enanos de las Bodegas vale el peso del general en oro, armaduras o cañones.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Behind the most abominable grime, there could be hidden the true military gem.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Detrás de la mugre más abominable, puede esconderse la verdadera joya militar.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: The Knightly Orders of the Southern Realms and their emulators are proud and fierce fighters, especially in service to the worthy.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Las Órdenes de Caballería de los Reinos del Sur y sus emuladores son orgullosos y fieros luchadores, especialmente al servicio de los dignos.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Swift and decisive maneuvers on the flanks are the trademark of an ambitious general.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Las maniobras rápidas y decisivas en los flancos son la marca de un general ambicioso.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: All generals need their trusted regiments.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Todos los generales necesitan sus regimientos de confianza.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Solid palisades, trenches, pavises, cannons, food, wine. The perfect ingredients for a successful siege, by Myrmidia!
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Empalizadas sólidas, trincheras, pavés, cañones, comida, vino. Los ingredientes perfectos para un asedio exitoso, ¡por Myrmidia!

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Don't ask them about living on the edge. Or huge green things with teeth.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: No les preguntes si viven al límite. O de enormes cosas verdes con dientes.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Be where the enemy expects you not.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Estar donde el enemigo no te espera.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Perhaps risen from the lowest ranks, this commander is in his own environment when leading mercenary companies, just as a dolphin plays on the waves.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Tal vez surgido de los rangos más bajos, este comandante se desenvuelve en su propio ambiente cuando dirige compañías de mercenarios, igual que un delfín juega sobre las olas.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: With roots and allies among the most powerful and upright nobility, this Lord doesn't often meddle with unstable mercs. Who heard that.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Con raíces y aliados entre la nobleza más poderosa y recta, este Señor no suele meterse con mercenarios inestables. Quién lo oyó.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Master of one of those small domains that make the Border Princes, this Lord can rely on his citizens and local supporters.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Señor de uno de esos pequeños dominios que forman los Príncipes de la Frontera, este Señor puede confiar en sus ciudadanos y partidarios locales.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Well-used to fierce struggles against countless invaders, this Lord has earned the trust of the Rangers.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Acostumbrado a las luchas encarnizadas contra innumerables invasores, este Señor se ha ganado la confianza de los Rangers.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Tileans are an odd bunch, known to fight to the last for the most disparate reasons: their ideals, their captain, their regiment, their purse, a painting.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Los tileanos son un grupo extraño, conocidos por luchar hasta el final por las razones más dispares: sus ideales, su capitán, su regimiento, su monedero, un cuadro.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: The Goddess of Battle protects Her own.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: La Diosa de la Batalla protege a los suyos.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: A commoner was once asked by a foreign recruiter about a band of Estalian mercenaries. Shrugging, he replied that they were "evil men", which was misunderstood as being 'local' for tough troops. Like many mistranslations, it stuck.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Un plebeyo fue preguntado una vez por un reclutador extranjero acerca de una banda de mercenarios estalianos. Encogiéndose de hombros, respondió que eran "hombres malvados", lo que se malinterpretó como "local" para referirse a tropas duras. Al igual que muchos errores de traducción, se quedó grabado.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: In one of the bloodiest pages of Tilean culture, the true mettle of a warrior is measured in the pit, for the amusement of the public. And Lorenzo is very entertaining.
The rulers of Luccini may be eccentric and a bit inbred, but Lorenzo is a great fighter at the head of the best pikes of Tilea.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: teb_lorenzo_lupo_innate

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Luccini commands the strongest fleet in Tilea and perhaps the strongest army as well.
They say that Luccinians will depose a Prince with poor humour. They take jokes seriously over there.
"Row row row your boat", they used to say, and Lorenzo can sweat and pull for miles.
Lupo likes to run to the edge of his Principality and back to the other border. And again.
Lorenzo may be a weird fellow with his obsession for the antiques and the ancients, but his physique surely reminds one of the impossibly-perfect statues literring Luccini.
"Mate of mine saw the Prince in the baths. He said he had an eight pack. Lorenzo is shredded."
"Oh my gods, but here goes Lorenzo with the Double Elbow Bonanza! What a match!"
Lucrezzia's manipulation over military champions and leaders leads to survival of the fittest.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: La manipulación de Lucrezzia sobre campeones y líderes militares conduce a la supervivencia del más fuerte.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Every rose has its thorn. This one in particular, a handy dagger and several hired guardians as well.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Toda rosa tiene su espina. Esta en concreto, una daga muy útil y varios guardianes a sueldo también.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Lucrezzia may consolidate her relationship with Xavier Rothemuur, current ruler of the northern port and expatriate member of House Rothemuur of Marienburg. Lucrezzia would secure the support of not one, but two wealthy City-States, but the other rulers of Estalia may definitely perceive her as a threat.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Lucrezzia podría consolidar su relación con Xavier Rothemuur, actual gobernante del puerto norteño y miembro expatriado de la Casa Rothemuur de Marienburgo. Lucrezzia se aseguraría el apoyo no de una, sino de dos ricas Ciudades-Estado, pero los demás gobernantes de Estalia podrían percibirla definitivamente como una amenaza.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: The previous seven husbands of Lucrezzia's have always been useful and influential men, until they stopped being such. During these dire circumstances of exile, the new consort must be especially... supportive.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Los siete maridos anteriores de Lucrezzia siempre han sido hombres útiles e influyentes, hasta que dejaron de serlo. Durante estas terribles circunstancias de exilio, la nueva consorte debe ser especialmente... solidaria.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: ...Or maybe not. Having a lot of suitors, especially the influential ones, may open a lot more doors than only one.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: ...O tal vez no. Tener muchos pretendientes, especialmente los influyentes, puede abrir muchas más puertas que uno solo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Marrying the eccentric ruler of Magritta would make for an interesting life and a hand on the wheel of the powerful city, but it would also antagonize Lucrezzia's Tilean compatriots.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Casarse con el excéntrico gobernante de Magritta le proporcionaría una vida interesante y una corona conjunta sobre las dos ciudades estalianas más poderosas, pero también enemistaría a los compatriotas tileanos de Lucrezzia.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Tibaldus Marsarius de Vela, current Prince of Tobaro and powerful banker. His city is a safe port and cosmopolitan center that is certainly very promising in the right hands. However, Magritta's rulers would feel threatened.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Tibaldus Marsarius de Vela, actual Príncipe de Tobaro y poderoso banquero. Su ciudad es un puerto seguro y un centro cosmopolita ciertamente muy prometedor en las manos adecuadas. Sin embargo, la reclamación de Magritta sobre ella provocaría una fuerte reacción.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Oh, so much can be done with a letter here, a smile there, or more audacious initiatives. The Lady of Pavona's ability to maintain her web of connections is powerful and precious in this world.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Oh, se puede hacer tanto con una carta aquí, una sonrisa allá o iniciativas más audaces. La habilidad de la Dama de Pavona para mantener su red de conexiones es poderosa y preciosa en este mundo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: The Lady of Pavona is famous, among other things, for kissing the weapon of today's champion before his duel or battle. Of course, her lipstick is terribly poisonous.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: La Dama de Pavona es famosa, entre otras cosas, por besar el arma del campeón de hoy antes de su duelo o batalla. Por supuesto, su pintalabios es terriblemente venenoso.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Discreetly poisoning the enemy commanders the night before battle is... well, just another continuation of diplomacy, like war itself.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Envenenar discretamente a los comandantes enemigos la noche antes de la batalla es... bueno, otra continuación de la diplomacia, como la guerra misma.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Another secret recipe of Lucrezzia's, this concoction will greatly improve the imbiber's strength and resilience. Maybe, just maybe, also poison them. A bit.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Otra receta secreta de Lucrezzia, este brebaje mejorará enormemente la fuerza y resistencia del imbibidor. Tal vez, sólo tal vez, también los envenene. Un poco.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Lucrezzia always wears, somewhere on her person, a dagger coated with another of her brews. Can't blame someone for being prepared for a midnight stab.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Lucrezzia siempre lleva, en algún lugar de su persona, una daga recubierta con otro de sus brebajes. No se puede culpar a nadie por estar preparado para una puñalada a medianoche.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "Ride with me? In broad daylight? Dear, you are far too unimportant for that."
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "¿Montar conmigo? ¿A plena luz del día? Querida, eres demasiado poco importante para eso".

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: A false promise here, a shift of alliances there, and the enemy has no idea it's not an ally anymore.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Una falsa promesa aquí, un cambio de alianzas allá, y el enemigo no tiene ni idea de que ya no es un aliado.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Some people mistake Lupio's battlefield antics for astute shows of force and bravery for the troops. Truth is, they're Lupio's own satisfaction.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Algunas personas confunden las payasadas de Lupio en el campo de batalla con astutas demostraciones de fuerza y valentía para las tropas. La verdad es que son la propia satisfacción de Lupio.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Good handguns are the future of warfare, if only these wretched peasants wouldn't whine so much about having to pay for them.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Las buenas pistolas son el futuro de la guerra, si tan sólo estos miserables campesinos no se quejaran tanto por tener que pagar por ellas.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Perfect uniforms and incessant drills, that's the stuff.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Uniformes perfectos y ejercicios incesantes, eso es lo suyo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: A cloak made of Lustrian gold, with uncertain magic properties. Its known feature is to give Lupio immense satisfaction.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Capa de oro lusitano con propiedades mágicas inciertas. Su característica conocida es que proporciona a Lupio una inmensa satisfacción.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Estalians are notoriously fascinated by the gold overseas. Lupio is more interested in the gold over himself.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Los estalianos están notoriamente fascinados por el oro de ultramar. A Lupio le interesa más el oro que él mismo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Lupio's own demigryph owes his companionship to Lupio and "Big Magpie" nickname to his distinctive black and white coat and attraction towards shiny baubles.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: El semigrifo de Lupio debe su compañerismo a Lupio y su apodo de "Gran Urraca" a su característico pelaje blanco y negro y a su atracción por las chucherías brillantes.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Nothing shines as bright as the man in gilted armour who insists on having telescopes aimed at himself.
They stink, and really they don't know any better than living in muddy shacks. Also, something should be done about their wretched windmills.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Apestan, y en realidad no conocen nada mejor que vivir en chozas de barro. Además, habría que hacer algo con sus miserables molinos de viento.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Reaped during a confusing skirmish against reptiles, elf corsairs and marauders, this ring bears an eerie and intriguing aura over it. Inquisitors never managed to get it off Lupio for investigation.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: Cosechado durante una confusa escaramuza contra reptiles, corsarios elfos y merodeadores, este anillo lleva sobre sí un aura inquietante e intrigante. Los inquisidores nunca consiguieron quitárselo a Lupio para investigarlo.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Magrittan naval prowess accepts very few rivals. Begrudgingly.
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: La proeza naval de Magrittan acepta muy pocos rivales. A regañadientes.

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: "I had actually sent to buy a unicorn. Made of diamonds. Like, a real live unicorn made of diamonds, very stylish. But they say it can't be done. Unimaginative buggers, the lot of them."
character_skills_localised_description_t.value_translated: "Había mandado comprar un unicornio. Hecho de diamantes. Como, un unicornio de verdad hecho de diamantes, muy elegante. Pero dicen que no se puede hacer. Son unos cabrones sin imaginación".

character_skills_localised_description_t.value_original: Lupio has secretly concocted the perfect plan to dramatically improve the region's welfare.
